text: 146 (one hundred forty-six) is a natural number. It comes after 145 and before 147. == In mathematics == *Composite number: 146 is not a prime number because it has more than two factors. *Semiprime: It is the product of two prime numbers: 146=2×73. *Even number: Because it ends in 6, 146 can be divided by 2. *Deficient number: The sum of its proper divisors (1, 2, and 73) is 1+2+73=76, which is less than 146. == Digital sums == The sum of its digits (1 + 4 + 6) is 11. The product of its digits (1 × 4 × 6) is 24. ==Different ways to write 146== *Roman numerals: CXLVI *Binary (base 2): 10010010 *Octal (base 8): 222 *Hexadecimal (base 16): 92 Category:Integers
